From 050a394e7748908d5555fb6f519c749dfd9c18f4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Igor Kanyuka <ifelmail@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 24 Feb 2025 12:50:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 201/205] Add generation for Vendor registries and a DBus to RF
 map

The system consumes Log events sent over DBus, but these events
do not have Redfish message IDs, so they cannot be used directly.
The definitions in the phosphor-dbus-interfaces repo allow to map
a DBus event to redfish messages IDs, so generate a map that can
be consumed in BMCweb.
The phosphor-dbus-interfaces repo also allows to use OpenBMC
vendor registries, consume this info and generate vendor registries
along with the DMTF ones.

Note, phosphor-dbus-interfaces define things in Yaml and json
representation is generated as part of build process. So, to make the
script generate files, the phosphor-dbus-interfaces should be checkout
and built before scripts/parse_registries.py is executed.
In the future, this and the script execution might/should be automated:
- phosphor-dbus-interfaces is added as a dependency
- scripts/parse_registries.py is executed as part of the build process

Testing:
Ran the script, and it generated vendor registries and the map.

